{"type":"message","id":"8c132cd1","parentId":"d5be5df2","timestamp":"2026-04-06T12:15:35.141Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_eoBiXCW4aXhg0cZdHurtJc4H","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## Search: crypto SEC latest enforcement ETF filing site:sec.gov\n**Engine**: tavily\n\n### Answer\n\nThe SEC recently enforced a rule for the Rowe Price Active Crypto ETF under NYSE Arca Rule 8.201-E. The SEC clarified federal securities laws application to crypto assets in 2026. The ProShares CoinDesk Crypto 20 ETF seeks to track the CoinDesk 20 index.\n\n---\n\n### Results (5)\n\n- **Order | U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission** (62%)\n  https://www.sec.gov/taxonomy/term/193081\n  Latest Filings · Mutual Fund Search · Variable Insurance Products Search · SIC ... Rowe Price Active Crypto ETF under NYSE Arca Rule 8.201-E (Non-Generic)\n\n- **Cyber, Crypto Assets and Emerging Technology** (45%)\n  https://www.sec.gov/about/divisions-offices/division-enforcement/cyber-crypto-assets-emerging-technology\n  The SEC's Crypto Task Force seeks to help the Commission provide clarity on the application of the federal securities laws to the crypto asset\n\n- **485A** (38%)\n  https://www.sec.gov/Archives/edgar/data/1174610/000119312525243764/f43079d1.htm\n  ProShares CoinDesk Crypto 20 ETF (the “Fund”) seeks investment results, before fees and expenses, that track the performance of the CoinDesk 20\n\n- **Press Releases** (38%)\n  https://www.sec.gov/newsroom/press-releases\n  March 17, 2026, SEC Clarifies the Application of Federal Securities Laws to Crypto Assets, 2026-30 ; March 17, 2026, SEC Publishes Data on Public and Private\n\n- **Defiance Crypto ETFs 485A** (38%)\n  https://www.sec.gov/Archives/edgar/data/1540305/000089418925006986/defiancecryptoetfs485a.htm\n  The Fund seeks to capture the yield generated from the futures basis (the premium generated from the difference between the bitcoin spot price and the futures"}],"details":{"status":"com